        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00 Yunnan/9–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Kumming</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lutkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kunming</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-15">September 15,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received September 15—2:06 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>159. Arrests of “reactionary elements” continuing. Midnight curfew in force for
                    indefinite period and all meetings banned. All universities and middle schools,
                    public and private, dissolved on orders of Executive Yuan pending screening of
                    teachers and students and reorganization.</p>
                <p>Sent OffEmb Hong Kong 62; repeated Department 159, American Consul Chungking
                    9.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Lutkins</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
